title: Biden Continues Economic Appeal Amid Conflict in Israel
description: The president continued to hold events on economic issues while managing the conflict between Israel and Hamas, hoping to appeal to Americans focused on pocketbook concerns.

title: E.U. Probes Elon Musk’s X Platform Over Violent Israel-Hamas War Content
description: Regulators are examining whether X violated a new European law that requires large social media companies to stop the spread of illegal content, disinformation and other harmful material.

title: Friday Briefing: The U.N. Warns of Disaster in Gaza
description: Plus a new comic book universe.

title: As Warnings of Crisis in Gaza Mount, Palestinians Struggle to Find Room for the Dead
description: Israel’s latest strikes on Gaza have drawn warnings from aid workers and residents of a humanitarian catastrophe. “We are facing a huge disaster,” said one U.N. official.

title: As Israel Prepares for War in Gaza, Debate Is Over How and How Long
description: The country’s new unity government agrees that Hamas must be destroyed so it can never attack Israel again, but there is little appetite for a reoccupation.

title: A Look at Disinformation Around Israel Attacks and False Claims on Social Media
description: Graphic imagery and footage have flooded social media since Hamas terrorists attacked Israelis. Bogus claims are also circulating and risk obscuring real evidence of atrocities.

title: Blinken Stresses Support for Israel While Urging Restraint on Gaza Airstrikes
description: During a visit to Tel Aviv, Secretary of State Antony J. Blinken promised to help defend the country “as long as America exists.”

title: Laszlo Solyom, a Transitional President of Hungary, Dies at 81
description: A noted legal scholar, he helped lead his country away from Communism after the fall of the Soviet bloc but could not stop its embrace of right-wing populism.

title: Stockholm to Ban Diesel- and Gas-Powered Vehicles in City Center in 2025
description: The new low-emission zone appears to be the most ambitious in Western Europe, and it is set to become law in little more than a year.

title: For NATO, 3 Pressing Questions After This Week’s Meetings
description: Defense ministers went home without resolving the status of Sweden, determining who attacked a Baltic Sea pipeline or how to respond to Israel’s war with Hamas.

title: Egypt Offers No Exit as Deaths Soar in Gaza From Israeli Strikes
description: Gazans are blocked from fleeing through Egypt, which has kept tight control of its border. An Israeli invasion of Gaza could test President Abdel Fattah el-Sisi’s approach.

title: Israel, Gaza and the Laws of War
description: International law offers a framework for how to analyze what is happening.

title: Family of Israeli Hostage Marks Her Birthday While Mourning Her Friend
description: For Noa Argamani’s 26th birthday, her family held a dinner with cake and two empty chairs: one for her and one for her boyfriend. Both were seen on video being kidnapped by Hamas.

title: Ukraine and Russia Try to Use Israel-Hamas War to Sway Opinions
description: Kyiv says Russia is looking to leverage the Israel-Hamas war to dampen support for Ukraine, while Moscow is calling it a failure of the West.

title: This Gaza Hospital Is Running Short on Fuel and Beds
description: Staff members are scrambling to treat the wounded, who are crammed into corridors that are also filled with people who fled their homes amid Israeli airstrikes.

title: UN Official Warns of ‘Huge Disaster’ in Gaza
description: Water and electricity supplies have been cut off, and the status of emergency humanitarian aid is unclear, said a spokesman for a U.N. agency working in Gaza.

title: Japan Seeks to Dissolve Unification Church After Abe Killing
description: The assassination of Shinzo Abe, the country’s longest-serving prime minister, shed light on the fringe group’s political ties and manipulation of its followers.

title: Israel-Hamas War: Israel Prepares for ‘Next Stage of War’ as Blinken Arrives in Tel Aviv
description: Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu formed an emergency unity government with the opposition and pledged to “crush and eliminate” Hamas.

title: New Zealand’s Maori Party Uses Fashion as a Political Weapon
description: Politicians typically swat away questions about their appearance, but Te Pati Maori has wielded fashion as a political weapon.

title: What to Know About the New Zealand Election
description: Voters head to the polls this weekend in an election that is likely to show a rightward and populist shift in the country’s politics.

title: Thursday Briefing
description: Israel’s unity government.

title: In Russian Military Town, Patriotism and Pathos Live Side by Side
description: The contradictions of Vladimir Putin’s war are changing the face of towns with military bases in Russia. Patriotism and pride are abundant, but so are sadness and death.

title: Is Daniel Noboa the Answer to Ecuador’s Need for Change?
description: Daniel Noboa, a center-right businessman whose family business includes a globally known banana brand, is facing an establishment leftist, Luisa González, in Sunday’s presidential election.

title: In Paris, Bedbugs and Fear of Bedbugs
description: Exterminators in France are playing the role of therapist to an anxious post-pandemic population that they say is panicking over recent bedbug outbreaks.

title: Vatican Conference Draws All Stripes to Rome, Welcome or Not
description: A major meeting to discuss sensitive issues in the Catholic Church is being held with the utmost secrecy and discretion. Outside, it’s a different story.
